<h2>The weather in March 2021</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
Temperatures were much above average in Norway and Sweden and on the British Isles. On the contrary, southeastern Europe was colder than average. In France and Germany the contrast in weather patterns was large, with cold weather at the beginning of the month and very mild weather at the end of the month, resulting in (much) below average minimum temperatures and (much) above average maximum temperatures.
