<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
Especially northeastern France, North and Central Italy, Northwest Spain, and the coast of Slovenia and Croatia had a high global and shortwave radiation anomaly together with a negative cloud cover anomaly. In Norway and Sweden the radiation was slightly lower than average.
